Organisers of the Hollywood and African Prestigious Awards (HAPAwards), recently presented Fuji maestro, Wasiu Alabi Pasuma with the award for Best International Music Video 2021. The HAPA team also used the unique opportunity to attend a groundbreaking ceremony of the Wakanda-One city initiative in Ghana. The award presentation led by Producer and African Representative of HAPAwards, Adeola Odunowo, was held at the singer’s home in Lagos.   Miracle Nduka breaks new grounds     The Queen of Flow returns for Season 2     SiSobola promises to always put smiles on people’s faces   While expressing his gratitude to the award organisers, Pasuma said it was an amazing experience to be a part of the last edition at the Orpheum Theatre in Los Angeles, California. “Winning this category only goes to show that I am still relevant in the music industry and I desire to even contribute more than I have. God bless you all,” Pasuma said. Speaking during an interactive session, the Founder and Executive Producer of HAPAwards, Ms. Tina Weisinger said, “There is no better time to unite the Black race as it’s evident that Africa is the last frontier of human development. Our platform will continue to support and encourage talents and creativity across the globe.”